definition.value: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is the conjugate base of alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosylceramide.
A 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxy group of (R)-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid.
Pentaanion of (3S)-citramalyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions.
Tetraanion of but-2-enoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
Conjugate base of 4-oxoproline.
An L-amino acid anion, being the conjugate base of L-3-oxoalanine.
Conjugate base of L-2-aminoadipic acid.
Tetraanion of ADP-D-ribose 2'-phosphate.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of D-fructofuranose 1-phosphate.
Dianion of O-phospho-L-threonine.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of (25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.

A tricarboxylic acid trianion that is the tricarboxylate anion of luteolin 7-O-[(beta-D-glucosyluronic acid)-(1->2)-(beta-D-glucosiduronic acid)] 4'-O-beta-D-glucosiduronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate acid of 17-O-acetylajmaline.
An O-phosphonatooxyserine(2-) that is the dianion of O-phospho-D-serine.
Conjugate base of 5-phospho-beta-D-ribosylamine.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of 6-hydroxypseudooxynicotine, obtained by protonation of the secondary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfonate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the sulfo and carboxy groups of 3-sulfolactic acid.
Conjugate base of 3-epi-3-hydroxy-2'-deoxymugineic acid.
Conjugate base of 3''-deamino-3''-oxonicotianamine.
A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is the conjugate base of chlorophyllide b, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
Dianion of pheophorbide a.
A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is the conjugate base of divinyl chlorophyllide a, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
Dicarboxylate anion of (1R,6R)-2-succinyl-6-hydroxycyclohexa-2,4-diene-1-carboxylic acid.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-imazaquin. It is a pre- and post-emergence herbicide used for the control of grasses and broad-leaved weeds.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxy group of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetyl-beta-muramic acid.
Conjugate base of (4R,5S,6R)-2,4,5,6-tetrahydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-one.
Dicarboxylate anion of (R)-2-benzylsuccinic acid.
Dicarboxylate anion of (7R)-7-(4-carboxybutanamido)cephalosporanic acid.
A organophosphate oxoanion that is the tetraanion of D-tagatofuranose 1,6-bisphosphate.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of D-tagatofuranose 6-phosphate.
Conjugate base of flaviolin.
Conjugate acid of (2R,4S)-2,4-diaminopentanoic acid.
The trianion of molybdopterin obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and 7-SH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
L-methionine (S)-S-oxide residue protonated on nitrogen.
An imidazolidine that is N-nitroimidazolidin-2-imine bearing a (6-chloro-3-pyridinyl)methyl substituent at position 1.
Conjugate acid of 6-(alpha-D-glucosaminyl)-1D-myo-inositol.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups of phosphoenolpyruvic acid.
Conjugate acid of 7-aminomethyl-7-deazaguanine.
Tetracation of 3,3,3-tetramine.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from deprotonation of the carboxy group of N-acetyl-beta-neuraminic acid.
L-methionine (R)-S-oxide residue protonated on nitrogen.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranose, arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate group and protonation of the amino group.
Dianion of UDP-4-deoxy-4-formamido-beta-L-arabinopyranose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate function.
Dianion of UDP-beta-L-threo-pentopyranos-4-ulose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate function.
Zwitterionic form of 4-amino-4-deoxy-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl undecaprenyl phosphate.
Tetraanion of lipid A arising from deprotonation of both phosphate functions  (R can be either hydrogen or a fatty acyl group).
Zwitterionic form of 7-chloro-L-tryptophan.
Dianion of beta-L-Ara4N-lipid A arising from deprotonation of both phosphate functions and protonation of the amino group  (R can be either hydrogen or a fatty acyl group).
